In the end, I... avoided the battle with Zuuteruka.

I didn't take his sweet words at face value that he wouldn't
harm Lord Yuia and the others if I didn't oppose him, but at
that time, it seemed like the only option I had.

I have no pride or certainty that the path I chose was the
right one.

I think it's because the path I chose wasn't something I
desired and seized for myself, but rather a result of
'having no other choice.'

It's something very heavy that I carry on my back... but
it's also very precious.

Throwing away such things... I chose a path as if running
away.

What kind of face will I live with from now on? What kind of
thoughts and worries will I carry with me?
Right now... I don't know.
The only thing I do know...

Is that there will definitely be no smile there. Living with
a dead heart harbored in this sinful body.
Yet... time passes by equally for everyone.
Whether my heart dies or lives... time will pass by.
